cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.LG

The paper focuses on automatic detection of cyberbullying in social media text, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the problem of information overload on the web, which suggests a possible connection to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The topic of cyberbullying is related to cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing technologies. The use of machine learning algorithms for classification falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
